The menu of a fat addicted child: It does not eat breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have problems with obesity, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have shown that obese children are mostly from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important the environment is for a person's healthy development, in which he grows up and are the examples that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more common on the table than in families where normal - weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had fries for dinner the day before the educational campaign under the motto "Adiposity is no coincidence".
In families with fat children, sport is also not one of the favourite activities, which also affects the majority of today's students - only 15 percent replied that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
Survey of 900 Children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, and nearly 900 children from primary schools throughout the Czech Republic were surveyed.
This was already the second year of the "Adipositas is not a coincidence" campaign, which is supported by the general health insurance fund and the Unilever company.
To date, more than 12 thousand students from 4th and 8th grades have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are decisive factors that are responsible for the alarming increase in the number of overweight or even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed, for example, said eating breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-vesper dinner five times a day - one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet," says one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that also relative small things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the pupils' families have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone has breakfast for themselves.
Worst of all was the statement that one in ten families does not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is considered to be the cornerstone of healthy daily nutrition.
Among other things, the survey test revealed that in the families of overweight children, unhealthy fries are often consumed.
And almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed do sports, only less than half of their parents do so - only 15 percent.
Set up your own menu
Another part of the survey made it possible for selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to come up with their own menu from the possibilities offered by appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of diet is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many pastries, meat dishes and, of course, desserts.
"Alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet lemonades", is emphasized in the final report to this survey.
At lunch, the main dish, pasta won just before poultry.
The children almost didn't like pulses and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Returning to Health
At the same time, however, the survey also showed that children are quite willing to change their eating habits when they get the right information.
"In the control group of the survey participants who completed the questionnaire after completing the enlightening lecture "Adiposity is not a coincidence" there was in many cases a marked shift in preferences towards principles of healthy nutrition", is stated in the results of the project.
This was eye-catching, for example, with the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
In the questionnaire, the children also crossed poultry or fish much more frequently as the main dish of the day and were ready to eat less dumplings or sweet food.
Pros claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article on how stylists learn, I had a bit moaned that this was a bit too much stuff to start with.
I didn't know in the least what was coming.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar on how the "on the square" is going.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer we get to the test, the more information and practical tasks ahead of us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully occupied.
This time we discussed with director Alena (not a single man participates in the course) how to attract a woman who does not have an ideal proportioned figure.
And that's what most of us are.
Some have too short a neck, others have too young a figure without proper curves and others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to conceal wide shoulders visually, extend the neck or conjure up the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to attract a female type like Jennifer Lopez - i.e. with a big bosom, wide hip and narrow waist - pretty and figure-hugging, without her being too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so big that the skirt or pants really don't fit, you should at least have a piece tailored to your needs.
You won't regret that, because well-fitting clothing is simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt, you feel much better than in one of the poles, which is getting too high and slippery, standing at the waist, etc.
Young figures can in turn allow themselves to wear clothing with wrinkles, pads, applications, embroidery or ruffle.
With this amount of information and figure types, I am glad that I have a whole week to let everything go through my mind thoroughly.
And yet I'm afraid that it's almost impossible to do it in the face of the assigned homework.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity for whom she was supposed to create suitable outfits - daywear and evening robe.
We should take into account the current look, the fashion style of the corresponding star and its figure type.
I'm supposed to "dress" Miranda Kerr, whom you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
On the inside I cheer, because this is much better for me personally than, for example, putting on Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably increased to a hundred kilos in recent times (well, that's a bit exaggerated), or also the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut out the clothes from magazines or search the internet, print them out and then edit them graphically.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design are to be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models physically, but also shapes the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example trend handbags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about this.
But it's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall view.
The Saturday lecture filled with information about figure types was seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And sent in stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in quite different ways.
The magic word is called variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat as usual over the jeans, like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and immediately the whole look looks completely different.
"Play with it," he stressed.
But most of all, the following advice came to mind: "First, you must know the rules perfectly."
"Only then will you be allowed to hurt her," Jakub said.
At last I realize why we have to timpani all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see quite different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more types of clothing than he finally photographed.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
So you have to reckon with all this in the design of the outfit.
Jan Pokorný confirmed that image and styl sometimes make up half of the success.
You just have to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are rather reserved.
Also well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown out money (the main thing is that I bring something as I look at it is secondary).
And if one of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she will most likely impose a completely different (smaller) size on us than he or she really needs.
Then all you have to do is google to find out for sure that the tabloid press writes that the appropriate celebrity has returned to or lost, etc.
Jan and Mario urged us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "build" the outfit.
In his work, he has to communicate with the people he styles and he has to be a clever psychologist.
To judge people without bending and standing up to his opinion.
"If any manager orders us to sift through her wardrobe and add some pretty pieces, then we can't clean out the whole closet and say - my God, that's terrible."
"You have to find at least a few praiseworthy things to which you recommend what you can contribute," says Mario.
He also showed us very concretely what such a so-called "place bag" must contain.
So this is a bag that you button at the waist and carry with you all the necessary proprieties.
In addition to such clear things as scissors, hair-removing wrappers or safety pins, it also contains utensils such as a nylon thread (which helps the stylist photograph products, such as handbags or hats), special clips that are used to pick up clothes in the back if it is too large (pins or other clamps are prohibited so that the fabric does not break) and, of course, sewing tools.
In order not only to listen, but also to try something out in practice, we learned how to properly glue shoes.
Also while photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, one can damage the sole of the shoe, let alone the outside.
We were stuck and glued...
With scissors you must not even touch the shoes, so that you do not damage them.
So you really have to be clever.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned is not exactly my strength.
All this was only a fraction of what we heard at the second weekend-continuation course.
One thing has become clear to me now - to devote yourself to styling on a professional level is no child's play.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review
The originally carefree journey becomes a routine journey to the early shift due to a series of completely avoidable, dilettant errors.
Although it succeeded in fulfilling the ambitions to a large extent, what good is that, if obviously no one wanted to do a bit more?
Even before he came to the counters, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" raised high expectations.
After all, he promised to move the already year-old game series "Need for Speed" into a new dimension again and in the playable demonstration examples he did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about the fitting passages in which the main protagonist climbs out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you're used to with NFS, in the end, much is different than you expected.
Sure - potentially there are quite decent arcade races, but overall the game is diminished by some superfluous mistakes that have been present in this series for more or less a few years.
So there are actually no more mistakes, but rather signs of a basically incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure begins very well.
First of all, one is introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain problems of personal character; the only solution seems to be to take part in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, that is, on the west coast, you sit on the wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and in more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race takes place on a different track and that the individual stages take place in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
One has no moment the impression that game would offer the same over and over again.
Some environments are still very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the earlier parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the drive through the desert, through autumnal landscape or high up through deep snowy landscape looks visually very pleasant.
Every now and then atypical elements bring a little variety into the individual races.
In the desert, for example, one is surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts sight.
In the mountains, on the other hand, one has to watch out in hell that one is not buried by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are installed quite well in succession.
Only a few, but they're enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then you still expect a personal duel with a single opponent.
And the police get involved, too, trying to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty are passages where Jack leaves the car.
This is more about certain interactive animations in which Jack flees from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are much less passages in the game than one would expect (actually only three).
In the end, this is more of a benefit to the matter, because this element at least has no chance of getting bored - it belongs to the elements that make the game more varied in the context of the above.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today's point of view, it does not rip out trees, but on the other hand it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model continues to do quite well for action-packed racing, although one could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything's in perfect order.
Real problems only appear after a certain period of time.
In contrast to the driving model, the collision model is not entirely OK.
A game of this kind is hardly to be expected that it calculates complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have practically no idea before impact on any object how the car behaves, then obviously everything is not okay.
Typical example: In the narrow overtaking or passing by oncoming cars one "strips" at some places the other car only lightly, in other, almost identical situation one comes into the slingshot and turns wild pirouettes.
Or the car's about to crash.
Thanks to the Restart system, it doesn't matter, it's always annoying.
The restarts are solved like this: if you have total damage or land far off the track, then the game throws you back to the last clue of the track.
Only - in each race you only have five Restarts.
Once you've exhausted it, everything starts from the beginning.
So the Restarts are more like a tool, in case something doesn't succeed, but you shouldn't rely on it.
Sometimes, however, even the rest kind does not help, there nothing but to learn the critical section from the head.
Very unpleasant is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, have to be driven through in a very specific way, otherwise you simply do not fit through.
Elsewhere, at the appropriate point, you always encounter "civil" cars in the same configuration, whether you are the first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations when you see that the opponent is passing by two oncoming cars in front of one, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive around them or brake them.
And it doesn't matter when you get there, because everything is designed in such a way that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where one is always overtaken at the same place by the same opponent and here again without regard to the time.
This is the craziest way to complete the game on the long bridge that you pass in the opposite direction.
The opponent obviously has to get you out of here on the devil.
And if he's in front of you, then of course he takes the view, so that you drive your own car a few times in Klump.
Sure - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting but this intention is so clear that it quickly spoils the joy of the game.
And that's a pity, because despite the simpler driving model, the game is generally quite entertaining and sometimes so action-packed that you almost don't know where your head is.
And basically it doesn't matter what is "guilty" about it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in such a way that no boredom can arise, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the car change in the course of the races.
One must not overlook the petrol stations on the route, because right here you can change the car, although in most cases the car is sufficient, which you just have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for the urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
The task mode (challenges) also goes hand in hand with the mode of game history - i.e. the races in the individual locations you know from history.
Here there are not only medals, but also points of experience to gain for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and the history.
To get to the higher driver level, various items must be unlocked: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is at the same time connected with the online function Autolog, which compares among other things its own achieved results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
Another unintelligible carver is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you get by car into a subway tunnel (because of me), where you race in the dark on the rails long (because of me).
On the speedometer, numbers look between 150 a 200 km/h (because of me), but suddenly a subway comes from behind and drives one uncompromisingly to scrap.
In our editorial office we will probably argue for a long time about whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and here and there even brilliant.
All the more annoying is that at some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this applies in particular to accidents involving a greater number of people, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound reproduction is OK and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to address as broad a scale as possible rather young audiences, a soundtrack was created a lá "of everyone something" - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game was not diminished by the totally unnecessary mistakes mentioned above, we could have claimed with the boob tone that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But that's how the game seems kind of unfinished.
An in itself a great pleasure, but one should be prepared that these mistakes stick in your eyes with the power of airport headlights.
Concert of the "Students of the Velvet Revolution" with singing ensembles of the Charles University
The Festival Festa Academica now offers for the third time the combination of the World Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution and this together with the musical experience.
In the course of the festival, twenty professional and university choirs will present themselves.
The focus of the festival is on the two concerts that will take place on 17 November.
"Karlsuniversität has a large part to play in the festival."
"Among the participants is also the choir of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanistic Studies, and the festival committee includes Rector Václav Hampl," said Jakub Čaloun, head of the organizing team.
The absolute highlight of the festival is the public concert of technical school choirs, which takes place on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the square in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The programme includes the composition of the important Czech jazz musician Karel R
In the evening hours, the concert "Students of the Velvet Revolution" (Studenty Sametu) takes place in the gala rooms of the Volkshaus in Vinohrady, in which also university choirs perform, choirs of the Charles University are not excluded.
Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate the World Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to promote the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Association of Czech Choirs in cooperation with Johannes-Kepler-Gymnasium.
The entire event was sponsored by Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Václav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
In addition to festive concerts, the schedule also includes numerous music meetings, student cappanings, matinees and other events.
Detailed information can be found on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz
