The Prime Minister-designate, Mario Monti, will meet tomorrow with the President of Italy to present the new government, which is to face the crisis that has led Italy to the brink of economic collapse.
A statement from the Presidential Palace announced that the Monti appointed on Sunday would meet with President Giorgio Napolitano on Wednesday to confirm the formation of the government.
