Fujimori returned to the hospital for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, his family doctor informed.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for violation of human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several diseases, including tongue cancer, which is operated and controlled four times.
Alejandro Aguinaga, congressman and his personal doctor, told television that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the reason for his pain and muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons. Nevertheless, he did not wish for this because he considered him innocent.
He was operated four times on tongue cancer and he lost 18 kilos of weight. In addition, there are other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and blood circulation problems in the legs, the doctor counted.
Fujimori has been in the Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía detention centre since September 2007.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the Peruvian Army's death squad, which was secretly active during his reign.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political relations
An official delegation, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica and composed of several ministers and entrepreneurs, will start their visit to Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between the two countries and discuss political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet with his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón next Wednesday. According to the President of Uruguay, this will be the highlight of his busy schedule with politicians, businessmen and a meeting with the Uruguayan collective living in Mexico.
The meeting of both presidents in the city of Guadalajara "is suitable for the exchange of information on all policy areas between the two countries", announced the presidentship of the South American country on its website.
According to local media, Mujica is seeking Calderón's support for the incident with France when French head of government Nicolas Sarkozy put the South American country on a list of tax havens at the G20 summit in the French city of Cannes.
In his discourse, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that still act as tax havens, which Uruguay rejected and prompted a request from his ambassador to the European country.
Mexico has chaired the G20 since November, a group of the world’s most powerful emerging and industrialised countries. Since January of this year, there has been an agreement on the exchange of tax information to avoid double taxation with the South American country.
In recent years, the Government of Uruguay has tried to speed up the implementation of tax information exchange agreements in order to be removed from the "grey list" of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), which includes countries that have not adopted all international tax cooperation standards.
Since 2004, there has been a free trade agreement between Mexico and Uruguay at business level, which has contributed to a growing trade in goods between the two countries.
The purr-bearded installer enters the third dimension with "Super Mario 3D Land"
For 25 years Super Mario has fought tirelessly for the rescue of Princess Peach from the clutches of the evil Bowser, but never in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he fights for the love of the girl in stereo technology.
The game, which comes this month to the counters of all the world, has been tailored from the beginning to the characteristics of the portable console Nintende 3DS, with which can be played three-dimensionally without a special glasses.
"Mario is the figure who has to say how stereoscopy works without glasses," said Omar Álvarez, responsible for the Nintendo-specialized press in Spain, at the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Álvarez explained that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first Nintendo video game developed for this console from the very beginning" , because until now successful articles such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" have been adaptations of already existing titles.
Nintendo's spokesman underlined that although it was three-dimensional, "Super Mario 3D Land" was a "affordable" video game that allowed for a fast, fluid game.
Álvarez confirmed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contained two games in one: the first part is "light" to capture the less-spiced users.
After that, the experts can spin a "second round" over the different levels of games that are becoming increasingly difficult.
In addition, users can choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action. However, in order to overcome the obstacles without becoming victims of the "optical effects", they must always play three-dimensionally.
This trip of Super Mario into the three-dimensional world also means the return of the figure to a portable console, which has not been the case since 2005.
With this video game, Nintendo winks at the fans of the Saga and repeats the recipe for success of recent editions: The purr-bearded installer must overcome dangerously-picked platforms to free Princess Peach.
However, the player encounters news in the movements, the environment, the disguises and the enemies - and a "playable" Luigi.
Colom guarantees Portillo's extradition to the United States
The President of Guatemala, Álvaro Colom, announced this Tuesday that he would allow the extradition of former Governor Alfonso Portillo to take responsibility in the United States for the US $70 million money laundering conspiracy.
Thus the trial of the US application for extradition of Portillo ends, so that it can be brought to justice there.
In a press conference, Colom confirmed that his decision was based on the independence of the judiciary and the government, taking into account that a decision-making court had already ordered extradition.
He stressed that he had not interfered with court decisions during his government and had accepted all extradition requests he had been notified of.
Apart from Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín is being extradited for murder and assault, Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colom's action is a government act that takes place when all judicial and constitutional bodies are exhausted to condemn the former President of the State (2000-2004).
According to the decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court of Guatemala, Portillo must be extradited when his legal situation is clarified in Guatemale and his human rights are guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted for embezzling 120 million Quetzales in the Ministry of Defense during his reign. This trial preceded extradition, but the minister objected and revived the case.
Trinijove has helped 6000 young people at risk of social exclusion
The organisation was set up to avoid the marginalisation of young people without vocational training.
The first 25 years of life of the social assistance organisation Trinijove have led to important results: in this quarter century, 6000 young people threatened with social exclusion were supported to find a way out of their difficult situation.
In addition, there are over a hundred jobs created for this social group.
On the occasion of the anniversary, an event was held yesterday in the former factory buildings of Fabra i Coats, attended by more than 300 people.
Trinijove was set up in 1986 in the district of Trinitat Vella with the aim of helping young people with low levels of education, without work, with drug problems at risk of marginality.
Yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu was attended by many leaders of institutions and institutions who worked with the association during these 25 years.
The participation of political representatives from different directions during election campaigns demonstrated the impartiality of Trinijove's work.
Besides the president of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Region of Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol participated in the celebrations of the former socialist minister of education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and currently left-green city councillor Ricard Goma.
The large hall of Fabra i Coats was also visited by the current Catalan Minister of Social Affairs and Family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and Jaume Lanaspa, Director General of the Social Works of La Caixa Savings Bank.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was born in very difficult times and that today's times are no less complicated, but he added that the work done so far is "a good basis".
For the President of the Generalitat, Trinijove is a model that knows how to fight against difficult circumstances and gives hope to people in difficulties.
"The economic crisis is nothing new for the association and the work it does," he explained.
Occupied house where giant parties were held was cleared
The owners of the house had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on Balmes No. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without any resistance.
Everything points to the fact that the nightmares of the neighbors of house No. 51 on the street Balmes have found an end.
Twelve people voluntarily left the building, which they had illegally occupied and in which they had organized huge festivals, which had driven the neighborhood to despair. The evacuation took place by judicial order without police intervention.
After the eviction, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be checked," confirmed the house manager.
The squatters, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the rest were inhabited - took with them the entire electrical system and part of the water supply. Moreover, they had painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
On the three lower floors huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage from it.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, told Europa Press that her business had decreased by 80% since the beginning of the occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the squatters made their unfair competition because they sold the drinks to three euros, while they cost 10 euros in the discotheque.
In addition, the owner of the leisure place had been reported by the neighbors for disturbance of rest, while according to her statement the noise did not originate from the visitors of the disco, but from the squatters and in particular from the guests of the festivals that were organized there, and which according to the angry neighbors became more and more in recent weeks.
The discotheque's manager explained that the harassment had been so severe that she agreed with the owner of the building not to have to pay rent for the last nine months.
Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that she had received more complaints from her neighbours in recent weeks.
Last week, the chairman of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in Barcelona's City Council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, called for the building to be cleared immediately and the problems of civil coexistence and of the urban area to be tackled.
He explained that only one floor of the building had been occupied before the summer, but that the squatters had penetrated all the floors of the building and almost all the apartments in the last few months. In some of them there had even been theft.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to take action against the anti-social acts in the building."
